definitions.definition: A fretted stringed instrument , similar to the guitar , having a bowl-shaped body or soundbox ; any of a wide variety of chordophones with a pear-shaped body and a neck whose upper surface is in the same plane as the soundboard , with strings along the neck and parallel to the soundboard.

main_definition: A fretted stringed instrument , similar to the guitar , having a bowl-shaped body or soundbox ; any of a wide variety of chordophones with a pear-shaped body and a neck whose upper surface is in the same plane as the soundboard , with strings along the neck and parallel to the soundboard.

definitions.definition: Thick sticky clay or cement used to close up a hole or gap, especially to make something air-tight .
A packing ring, as of rubber, for fruit jars, etc.
A straight-edged piece of wood for striking off superfluous clay from earth.
